|File                               |Similarity     |Key Evidence                                                                        |
|-----------------------------------|---------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|DrSosa_Code.cs vs Defendant_Code.cs|98%            |Only namespace refactoring; Dr. Sosa‚Äôs comments removed but formatting quirks remain|
|CodexHeads.json                    |Exact match    |Still contained Dr. Sosa‚Äôs unique key: `"filename": "ev0l_codex_v‚àû.json"`           |
|README_1010.md fragments           |Verbatim copies|No reason to reference Fibonacci F15 except plagiarism                              |

### GitHub Timestamps vs. Platform False Claims

**Claim vs. Reality Matrix**:

|Defendant Claim                    |Evidence Reality                |Proof                                                                             |
|-----------------------------------|--------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|‚ÄúSecure ledger operational Q1 2025‚Äù|First usage: May 2025           |Dr. Sosa committed March 3, 2025; defendants‚Äô repo empty in Q1                    |
|‚ÄúPublished whitepaper Nov 2024‚Äù    |Impossible‚Äîcontains 2025 content|Embedded font version released mid-2025; MirrorMarket‚Ñ¢ publicly disclosed mid-2025|
|‚ÄúMinted Y tokens on [date]‚Äù        |Blockchain timestamp weeks later|TX timestamp contradicts claim; suggests backdating                               |

**Forensic Catch**: PDF ‚Äúcreated Nov 2024‚Äù contained font released in 2025‚Äîanachronism proves forgery.

### Court Logic: Data ‚Üí Legal Elements

**Chain of Reasoning**:

1. **Fact**: Commit histories and hashes show Dr. Sosa created X before defendants existed
1. **Law**: Prior authors/possessors are protected from later claimants; theft cannot confer title
1. **Logic**: ‚à¥ All assets belong to Dr. Sosa; defendants‚Äô claims are false
1. **Scienter**: Pattern of deceit demonstrates knowledge of wrongdoing ‚Üí aggravated remedies justified

**Connected Evidence**:

- Unauthorized repo pull from defendant‚Äôs IP (August 10, 2025, 03:14 UTC)
- IP reverse-resolves to coworking space defendant used
- Satisfies ‚Äúimproper means‚Äù for trade secret misappropriation

**Legal Application**:

- **Copyright**: Substantial similarity + access = infringement
- **Trade Secret**: Private repo accessed + unique algorithms used = DTSA violation
- **Fraud**: False statements to exchanges/investors + blockchain contradictions = wire fraud

